TRIBUTES continue to pour in for NBA legend Kobe Bryant, who was killed in a helicopter crash on Sunday. Famous athletes, politicians and actors from all over the world have paid their tributes to Bryant. The 41-year-old, who was widely considered one of the greatest NBA players of all time, has been described as a "inspiration" for athletes across all over the world.  Social media has been filled with messages of condolence to the entire Bryant family who also lost Gianna, Kobe's 13-year-old daughter who was also killed in the crash. Among those leading the tributes was Bryant's former teammates at the Los Angeles Lakers, Shaquille O'Neal who described him as a "brother." "There’s no words to express the pain I'm going through with this tragedy of losing my niece Gigi & my brother," he tweeted."I love u and u will be missed. My condolences goes out to the Bryant family and the families of the other passengers on board. IM SICK RIGHT NOW."  